text: APIA Leichhardt Football Club is an Australian semi-professional soccer club based in Leichhardt, a suburb of Sydney. It competes in the National Premier Leagues NSW (NPL NSW). It was founded by Italian Australians and has a strong connection to Sydney's Italian community. The acronym "APIA" in the club's name stands for . Category:Soccer clubs in Sydney
